mainContentBody.jahia:value:
The 5th service pack of Jahia 5 is now available. Most of the enhancements are Patches fixing issues and optimizations such as:

  • Avoids ACL loop creation
  • QueryTag usage optimizations
  • Avoids security breaches that could provide access to system files
  • Fixes issue with container display between live and edit mode
  • Fixes Lucene problems on NFS
  • Deletes temporary files used by the import module
  • Better handling of the URL re-writing in the Bigtext field

 

This new Service Pack is available for download at http://extranet.jahia.com, the Jahia Customers Extranet*.

*To access this dedicated section you have to login with your Product Jira account. You must be a signed customer and/or partner to obtain access to the Extranet.

We are very glad to announce the launch of Jahia 6, Community Edition open for download at www.jahia.org, our new Community Website.

Jahia 6, Community Edition offers a WCM platform with even stronger document management and portal features, fully leveraging AJAX technology and best of breed Open Source components, with major enhancements in:

  • Web 2.0 Ajax powered user interface, in-line editing capabilities, support for Google Analytics, customizable toolbars, improved workflow, and a modified front-end template infrastructure

  • Document management support for the “Jackrabbit” JSR 170 content repository

  • Embedded Apache Plutot 2.0 library for improved support for the latest version of the Portlets Standard (JSR 286), and a centralized mashup repository.

“Jahia 6.0 introduces a lot of visible enhancements, but the most important changes are in the underlying framework. We have introduced the GWT framework through the UI, JCR content definitions, and a completely revised tag library, to make this version our best web content management solution to date,” said Serge Huber CTO of Jahia.
